note.p:
Of special interest in this text is the personal name Χαῦσος in lines 3 and 4 where the first edition had καὶ σοῦ. The initial letters of the word in both lines are much more conducive to chi than kappa. Moreover, the next letter in both instances must be upsilon, which curls to the right rather than drifting below the line to the left, as epsilon would. The name Χαῦσος is previously unattested outside Berenike, although it may be related to Χαῦς, a variant of the Egyptian name Χαοῦς;
TM NamVar 35484 and ΤΜ Νam 36055, respectively. there is also evidence for the name Χούσης in the papyri.
TM Nam 23718.
